Nakheel Plans to Offer Islamic Bonds End of June, Ittihad Says

-- B y   Z a h r a a   A l k h a l i s i
-- 
2011-05-23T05:12:17Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-23/nakheel-plans-to-offer-islamic-bonds-end-of-june-ittihad-says.html
Nakheel PJSC, the developer of palm-
shaped islands off Dubai’s coast, plans to offer 4.8 billion
dirhams ($1.3 billion) in Islamic bonds, or sukuks, to the
company’s trade creditors by the end of June,  Al Ittihad 
reported, citing Chairman Ali Lootah.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zahraa Alkhalisi in Abu Dhabi at 
 zalkhalisi@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Shaji Mathew at 
 shajimathew@bloomberg.net  